forward or in which their
cases were taken seriously.

02:19.466 --> 02:22.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And you compound that on
top of the issues with the
prominent football team.

02:22.400 --> 02:27.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, yes, the scope, it just
touches all aspects of higher
education and of sexual assault

02:30.166 --> 02:32.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on campus.

02:32.200 --> 02:35.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And what can the
NCAA do, and what can it
not do in cases like this?

02:35.966 --> 02:38.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAULA LAVIGNE: So, that's
a really good question.

02:38.400 --> 02:41.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, a lot of people -- if
you're not familiar with college
sports, it's important to know

02:41.700 --> 02:46.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that the NCAA is sort of
the arbiter over amateur
college athletics, right?

02:48.400 --> 02:53.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And their purpose is to
ensure fair competition
and amateurism, OK?

02:55.733 --> 03:00.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, a lot of people think
They want the NCAA to
do something about this.

03:01.333 --> 03:02.833 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Right?

03:02.833 --> 03:05.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There is a huge call for
the NCAA to address this.

03:05.200 --> 03:10.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the issue is
that sexual violence,
addressing sexual violence,
addressing just criminal

03:12.100 --> 03:15.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
