really isn't something that's
technically in the NCAA's

03:16.166 --> 03:18.700 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
wheelhouse.

03:18.700 --> 03:22.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so for people to
understand what their
scope is, it's important
to understand a particular

03:23.566 --> 03:28.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
term that the NCAA uses,
which is extra benefit, OK?

03:30.433 --> 03:33.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, and when we think of extra
benefits, we often think of
student athletes being given

03:35.800 --> 03:38.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
money from boosters or fancy
cars or allowed to basically
skate on a class, OK?

03:41.000 --> 03:45.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The NCAA, in this case, for
people who are - - people on
the outside who are familiar

03:47.533 --> 03:50.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
